p: In the District Court of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory holding terms at Seattle
In the matter of the application of C.A. Clayton et. al. for a writ of Habeas corpus etc.
Upon being advised of the agreement of Counsel representing both petitioners and respondents in the above named matter-
It is considered and adjudged that the writ of habeas corpus issued commanding J.E. Howell to produce the bodies of the petitioners named in the petion herein of file be quashed and set aside.
